    "date": "2017-11-21",
    "comment": "Rationale: Adult rat forebrains were isolated, homogenized and then centrifuged multiple times (including one spin with a sucrose gradient) to yield postsynaptic densities (PSDs). PSDs were then separated on a 1D SDS gel and 14 gel slices were cut from this gel. The slices were trypsinzied and then separated using LC-MS/MS. MS/MS spectra were then compared to the NCBI database using the Sequest algorithm to identify peptides. 374 proteins were found in the PSD.. Experimental description: Paper just specifies rat with no reference to strain in this paper or the cited papers about the protocol.",
